{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/html-meta-tag-viewport","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">meta name=viewport</code> is not part of any web standards, but most of the mobile browsers today have support for it. The <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/2011/WD-html-markup-20110113/meta.name.html\">meta tag</a> adds instructions to the browser about the page scaling on different devices. To optimize the webpage for mobile devices add:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>meta</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">name</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>viewport<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">content</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>width=device-width, initial-scale=1<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note: meta tag should be added in the <head> of HTML page.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The content <code class=\"language-text\">width=device-width</code> will set the width of the page the same as the device screen size and <code class=\"language-text\">initial-scale=1.0</code> will set the initial zoom on load. This means it will scale on different devices since the viewport(the visible area to the user) is different on the laptops, mobile phones, tablets. Omitting the <code class=\"language-text\">viewport</code> the browser will use a virtual viewport that will zoom out the website. So, it is always the best practice to add a viewport so the website will be optimized for different screens.</p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"The  is not part of any web standards, but most of the mobile browsers today have support for it. The meta tag adds instructions to the…","frontmatter":{"title":"HTML Meta tag viewport","date":"2020-06-17 22:56:16 +0200","categories":["html"],"tags":["html","tags","meta","viewport","meta-tag"],"description":null,"keywords":"html, tags, meta, viewport, meta-tag","author":"Zoran Pandovski","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":204,"height":132,"src":"/static/b470f7e2894cfeeffc06fe0270376933/02521/html.png","srcSet":"/static/b470f7e2894cfeeffc06fe0270376933/02521/html.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/html-meta-tag-viewport","date":"2020-06-17T20:56:16.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/html-meta-tag-viewport","nexttitle":"fatal git-write-tree error building trees","nextslug":"/fatal-git-write-tree-error-building-trees","prevtitle":"What is Doctype in HTML?","prevslug":"/what-is-doctype-in-html","tagList":["python","pandas","abstraction","OOP","Class","java","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variables","Constants","HTML5","Web development","tricks","NumpPy","array","NLP","libraries","text processing","go","golang","data-structure","optimization","java 7","Java 8","comparison","mkdir(make-dir) and rmdir(remove-dir command) command","nodejs","backend","frontend","postgres","mac","installation","games","gamedev","memory","html","bootstrap","web development","data","strings","final","finally","finalize","Git","GitLens","VS Code Extension","CSS","Images","Image Display","CSS Variables","JavaScript","sort","localeCompare","Responsive Fonts","CSS Fonts","interface","default meth